===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|balled}}, {{m|enm|ballid}}, {{m|enm|bald|t=bald}}, of {{unk|en|title=uncertain}} origin. Probably formed from {{der|en|enm|bal}}, {{m|enm|balle|t=ball, round object, knoll, head}}. Compare with {{cog|gmq-oda|bældet|t=bald}}.

Alternate etymology has {{cog|got|𐌱𐌰𐌻𐌰-|t=shining, grey (of body)}}, {{cog|ang|bǣl|t=fire, flame; funeral pyre}} (both from {{der|en|gem-pro|*bēlą}}), {{cog|sq|balë|t=white spot on the forehead}} and {{m|sq|ball|t=forehead}}.

